    "Therefore, the real-space superlattice is similarly rotated and expanded by 1/(2 sin(θ/2)).",
    "A good rule of thumb is that the moiré lattice constant is a M ≃ 14 nm at the magic angle θ ≃ 1.05 •.",
    "The real-space moiré lattice vectors associated with b1, b 2 are a 1, a 2.With the mBZ specified, we can now define the filling factor ν, which is 0 at charge neutrality, and increments by 1 whenever we add one electron per moiré unit cell.",
    "Solving the Continuum ModelAs written above, the BM Hamiltonian has been expressed as a matrix in the planewave basis, in which a plane-wave state with momentum p, layer l and sublattice σ is denoted as |p, lσ⟩.",
